### Area

_No response_

### Describe the bug

Problem Summary:
The UserStorageProviderModel model parameter passed to the ImportSynchronization.sync() method contains outdated/stale configuration data when the provider configuration has been updated in the Keycloak admin console, this is not a race condition, the stale configuration exists even after 30 minutes of config updation at UI.

### Version

26.3.2

### Regression

- [ ] The issue is a regression

### Expected behavior

The UserStorageProviderModel parameter should always contain the most up-to-date configuration data from the database when the sync() method is called.

### Actual behavior

When implementing a custom User Storage Provider that implements ImportSynchronization, the sync() method receives a UserStorageProviderModel parameter that contains stale configuration data. This occurs when:
- A user updates the provider configuration in the Keycloak admin console
- A synchronization is triggered (via scheduled sync)
- The model parameter passed to sync() still contains the old configuration values
- When triggered manually, it contains the new configuration values

### How to Reproduce?

Implement custom factory which extends UserStorageProviderFactory and override the sync method and check model being passed.

### Anything else?

Current workaround:
```
@Override
public SynchronizationResult sync(final KeycloakSessionFactory sessionFactory, final String realmId, UserStorageProviderModel model) {
    try (final var session = sessionFactory.create()) {
        final var realm = KeycloakModelUtils.runJobInTransactionWithResult(sessionFactory, currentSession -> {
            return currentSession.realms().getRealm(realmId);
        });
        final var refreshedModel = realm.getComponent(model.getId());
        if (refreshedModel != null) {
            model = new UserStorageProviderModel(refreshedModel);  // Use the refreshed model
        }
        // ... rest of sync logic
    }
    // ...
}
```
